point : condoning the use of barrier method of contraception would be implicitly condone casual sex since their primary function be within that context . this be particularly important since the catholic church's teaching on casual sex be not take particularly seriously already . any action , such a the catholic church allow the use of barrier contraception , that would promote casual sex in country with severe aids hiv problem , would be an incredibly irresponsible one . pope paul vi argue that when consider the consequence of method and plan for artificial birth control . let them first consider how easily this course of action could open wide the way for marital infidelity and a general lowering of moral standard . the church's current stance on barrier contraception , therefore , be the most responsible one1 . 1 pope paul vi . humanae vitae . 1968 . 4 
