point : the catholic church do not only forbid the use of barrier contraception but also of casual sex . the issue be not that the church be be irresponsible by ban the use of barrier contraception but that people be choose to follow some of the church's teaching but not others . pope benedict xvi argue aids be a tragedy that cannot be overcome by money alone , that cannot be overcome through the distribution of condom , which even aggravate the problem 1 . if people follow the church's teaching on casual sex as well a their teaching on barrier contraception , the aids epidemic would be dramatically decrease . given , therefore , that it also forbid any sex outside of marriage , the catholic church be totally justified in forbid barrier method of contraception2 . 1 wynne jones , jonathan . the pope drop catholic ban on condom in historic shift . the telegraph , 20 november 2010 , 5 2 pope john paul ii . evangelium vitae . 1995 . 6 
