point : catholics consider the first commandment give to them by god to be to 'multiply'1 . in light of this , anything that limit procreation , be it the use of contraception or even condone the use of contraception , be against god . it be important to remember that the catholic church's primary obligation be not to it people but to god . the church be , therefore , justify in any action where the alternative be go against what they believe to be the wish of god , even if it be harmful to the people of the church . 11 : 28 , the book of genesis , the bible . 
